#ðŸ” Why This Matters:
Even though the actual pod status (Running, Pending, etc.) is managed by Kubernetes and reflected in kubectl get pods, itâ€™s not a label by default. By manually labeling status=running, you're now able to:

ðŸ“Œ Filter and Group Resources by Logical State
Even if their real status changes later, your label helps with:

Group-based queries
Creating services or deployments with label selectors
Organizing resources for environments, automation, monitoring, etc.



